definition:
A man of the tribe of Gad living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Gen.46.16; 
 son of: Gad (H1410); 
 brother of: Ziphion (H6837), Haggi (H2291), Shuni (H7764), Eri (H6179), Arod (H0720) and Areli (H0692); also called Ozni at Num.26.16; 
Another name of ets.bon (אֶצְבּוֹן "Ezbon" H0675G)
 § Ozni  = "my ear (hearing)"
 son of Gad
